Eight months ago, Gus Worland weighed 140 kilograms and was a regular smoker and drinker. 

But on Monday morning, the Triple M breakfast radio host crossed the finishing line of the New York City Marathon where he was applauded by his best friend and inspiration, Hugh Jackman.

Jackman, 46, who has known the radio host for 40 years and challenged him to get fit and run the marathon in a bid to encourage him to get healthy, admitted that he had tears in his eyes when he saw Worland finish.

