'He did it! I think I saw the time as like six hours 35 or something and he cried like a baby as he crossed the line,' Jackman told Triple M.

'He was really emotional, man. It took everything for him. I said to him "which was the worst bit?" and he said "from K28 to 42". He just really struggled to get across and he made it, he crushed it.

'When he crossed that line, you saw what that cost him. I had tears in my eyes.' 

After being congratulated by Jackman, his wife Vicky and their three children - Jack, 14, Ella, 13 and Abi, 11 - the 45-year-old member of the Grill Team, told his co-hosts 'I've got to tell you, I'm feeling awful'.

