'I feel so bad mate, I could use other words, but you'd have to dump me,' Worland jested.

'I've made it and it's done now so I'm really pleased right now. I'm feeling good now, but it hurt the whole six odd hours.'

Jackman also took to social media to show his pride, sharing snaps and video of the moment he embraced and cheered for his childhood friend.

'From the line to enter our kindergarten classroom… to the line at the start of the NYC Marathon. Proud of you Gus Worland,' Jackman tweeted from the finishing line. 

